---
// src/pages/terms.astro
import PolicyLayout from '../layouts/PolicyLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../data/site';
---

<PolicyLayout
  title="Terms of Service - Cyber Alliance India | Built with Intent"
  description="These terms are designed to ensure a transparent and secure partnership as we manage your digital infrastructure."
  badge="Service Agreement"
  heading="Terms of"
  highlight="Service."
  lastUpdated="December 30, 2025"
>
  <p>
    Welcome to <strong>Cyber Alliance India</strong>. By engaging our services or using our
    website, you agree to the following terms. These terms are designed to ensure a transparent and
    secure partnership as we manage your digital infrastructure.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Scope of Managed Services</h2>
  <p>
    Cyber Alliance India provides engineering and IT services, including website development and
    ongoing maintenance.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>24/7 Monitoring:</strong> We utilize <strong>Uptime Kuma</strong> to monitor client
      websites 24/7. While we strive for maximum availability, uptime is subject to third-party
      infrastructure stability.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Project Specifics:</strong> Each project is unique. The specific deliverables,
      timelines, and costs are governed by individual project terms or Statements of Work (SOW).
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Infrastructure:</strong> Our operations are supported by providers like Cloudflare
      (Security) and GitHub (Deployment).
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Fees and Payment Terms</h2>
  <p>We believe in fair compensation for high-quality engineering work.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Late Fees:</strong> Invoices not paid by the due date will incur a late fee of
      <strong>5% of the total amount due</strong>.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Annual Adjustments:</strong> To account for inflation and rising infrastructure costs,
      Annual Maintenance Contract (AMC) fees will increase by <strong>5% annually</strong>.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Secure Payments:</strong> All transactions are handled securely via
      <strong>Cashfree</strong>. We do not store sensitive financial data on our servers.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Limitation of Liability</h2>
  <p>
    While we take every precaution to secure your digital assets, our liability is limited as
    follows:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Data Loss:</strong> Cyber Alliance India is <strong>not responsible</strong> for any
      data loss, corruption, or damage to the client, regardless of the cause. We recommend clients
      maintain independent backups.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Indirect Damages:</strong> We are not liable for any indirect, incidental, or
      consequential damages (such as loss of revenue) arising from service interruptions.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Security:</strong> While we implement industry-standard security via Cloudflare and
      Zoho Mail, no internet-based service is 100% immune to threats.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Termination of Service</h2>
  <p>
    Either party may terminate the service agreement with 30 days written notice. We reserve the
    right to suspend services immediately if payments are significantly overdue or if the service is
    used for illegal activities.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Governing Law</h2>
  <p>
    These terms are governed by the laws of India. Any disputes will be subject to the exclusive
    jurisdiction of the courts in Delhi, India.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Contact Us</h2>
  <p>
    If you have questions about these terms or wish to discuss a project-specific agreement, please
    contact us:
  </p>
  <p class="mb-0 text-sm">
    Email: <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`} class="text-blue-500">{SITE.email}</a>
  </p>
</PolicyLayout>
